

=Bio=

"Jake has an MSc in Energy Policy and Sustainability from Exeter University and a BA
(Hons) in International Relations from the University of the West of England, Bristol. Prior to starting his PhD research at SPRU, he interned at Regen SW and has worked with the Bristol Energy Network and the Centre for Sustainable Energy, to develop ‘community energy’ capacity in Bristol. He is interested in the particular context of community energy as a site of innovation for sustainability and the kinds of innovative activities happening there."
(http://grassrootsinnovations.org/2012/04/12/phd-innovation-journeys-in-community-energy-initiatives-jake-barnes/)

